article.headline: Auburn 74, Kennesaw State 62
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Frank Tolbert had 12 points, including nine in the first half, to help lead Auburn to a 74-62 win over Kennesaw State Tuesday night. Tolbert's nine points in the first half helped the Tigers (1-1) secure a 33-24 lead going into the half. Auburn dominated most of the second half, leading by as many as 20 points with 6:02 remaining. In a late surge Kennesaw State (0-2) chipped Auburn's lead down to 12 points with 1:59 left. But the deficit was too much for the Owls to overcome. Tolbert was one of six Tigers to score in the double figures. He was joined with 12 points by Korvotney Barber and Rasheem Barrett. DeWayne Reed and Quantez Robertson had 11 points each, while Lucas Hargrove added 10. Robertson also had eight rebounds and six assists while Tolbert had seven rebounds. The Owls were led by Ronell Wooten with 23 points and seven rebounds. Keonte Keith chipped in 13 points. The Owls struggled offensively without leading scorer Shaun Stegall. He suffered a strained quadriceps muscle earlier this week. Kennesaw State shot only 33 percent from the field.
